## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: How many equipment financing companies should I compare?**  
A: At least 3-4 to get a good sense of what's available. More than that gets confusing.

**Q: What's a reasonable approval time?**  
A: 1-2 weeks is standard. Anything faster means they might be less thorough. Anything longer means they're disorganized.

**Q: Should I choose the lowest interest rate?**  
A: Not automatically. Look at total cost, flexibility, approval speed, and customer service.

**Q: Can I switch financing companies mid-term?**  
A: Usually yes, but early settlement penalties might apply. Check this before signing.

**Q: What if my business is less than 2 years old?**  
A: Many financing companies work with newer businesses if you have consistent revenue and a clear business model.

**Q: Do equipment financing companies report to CTOS/CCRIS?**  
A: Most do. On-time payments help build your business credit score.

**Q: What happens if I miss a payment?**  
A: Most companies will work with you if you communicate early. Ignoring the problem makes it worse.

**Q: Can I finance multiple pieces of equipment at once?**  
A: Yes, most companies offer package deals for multiple equipment purchases.

